import pandas as pd
import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
import matplotlib.ticker as ticker

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    plt.figure(figsize=(6, 6))
    
    data['Date'] = pd.to_datetime(data['Date'], errors='ignore')
    plt.plot(data['Date'], data['CO2'])
    
    if len(plt.xticks()[0]) > 20:
        plt.gca().xaxis.set_major_locator(ticker.MaxNLocator(20))
    plt.xticks(rotation=45)
    
    plt.title("What is the trend of CO2 concentration over time?", wrap=True)
    return plt;

chart = plot(data)
chart.show()

import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
import matplotlib.ticker as ticker
import pandas as pd

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    plt.figure(figsize=(6, 6))
    plt.hist(data['CO2'], bins=20)
    plt.xlabel('CO2 Concentration (ppm)')
    plt.ylabel('Frequency')
    plt.title('What is the distribution of CO2 concentration?')
    
    if len(plt.xticks()[0]) > 20:
        plt.gca().xaxis.set_major_locator(ticker.MaxNLocator(20))
    
    return plt;

chart = plot(data)
chart.show()

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    plt.figure(figsize=(6, 6))
    plt.scatter(data['CO2'], data['adjusted_CO2'])
    plt.xlabel('CO2')
    plt.ylabel('adjusted_CO2')
    plt.title('What is the relationship between CO2 and adjusted CO2 concentration?')
    
    if len(plt.xticks()[0]) > 20:
        plt.gca().xaxis.set_major_locator(ticker.MaxNLocator(20))
    
    data['Date'] = pd.to_datetime(data['Date'], errors='ignore')
    
    return plt;

import pandas as pd
import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
import matplotlib.ticker as ticker

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    plt.figure(figsize=(6, 6))
    plt.boxplot(data['CO2'])
    plt.xticks([1], ['CO2'])
    plt.title("What is the average CO2 concentration level?")
    plt.axhline(data['CO2'].mean(), color='r', linestyle='--', label=f"Mean: {data['CO2'].mean():.2f}")
    plt.legend()
    return plt;

chart = plot(data)
chart.show()
